### STEP 1: Create a VM and Connect to Terminal

In this case, we are using SSH protocol. 
### STEP 2: Update The VM & Install The Necessary Dependencies
sudo apt update -y
java (Depending on the version needed for the application.)
sudo apt install maven -y

### STEP 3: Clone The Repository & Build the Application.
git clone "the repo"
cd into the File. 
mvn package.

### STEP 4:
cd into the target folder
ls to list the files in the target folder.
java -jar filename... SNAPSHOT.jar (Run this command with the snapshot file).

### STEP 5: Run the Application in the Browser.
Copy the Public Address and port number.
The application Should be Live.
